author: maxb
msg: Issue #1795 "svnadmin load wrongly computes copyfrom-rev" - fixes for the
common case (loading a single dumpstream). Problems remain when loading
multiple dumpstreams, but that's a great deal more complicated to fix.
Patch by Ling Li, with review and edits by me.
(struct parse_baton): Add rev_map for mapping from the old revisions
to the new revisions during repository loading. Add pool for memory
(new_revision_record): Store the current old -> new revision mapping.
(maybe_add_with_history): Extract new revision from rev_map if the
old revision is stored there. Otherwise, fall back to our old code.
